    "eyebrow": "Cultural Adaptations",
    "num": "07",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Adaptations</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Blending Mexican and Anglo Traditions in Texican Life</h2><ul><li>Texicans adopted Mexican customs such as language, religion, and law</li><li>Anglo settlers contributed farming techniques and frontier practices</li><li>This cultural blending created a unique Texican identity</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican culture was a hybrid, combining Mexican legal and religious traditions with Anglo-American frontier skills and social norms, resulting in a distinct regional identity. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican settlers celebrated Catholic holidays while using Anglo-style farming tools and methods.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify examples of cultural blending in Texican daily life and governance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Texican culture as purely Mexican or Anglo without recognizing hybridization.</p></div></div>",
