    "eyebrow": "Environmental Adaptations",
    "num": "10",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">10</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Environmental Adaptations</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Strategies for Managing Frontier Environment</h2><ul><li>Settlers adapted farming techniques to local soil and climate conditions</li><li>Water management was critical due to variable rainfall and droughts</li><li>Livestock grazing practices balanced resource use and sustainability</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans developed environmental knowledge and practices to cope with the challenges of the Texas frontier, ensuring survival and economic productivity. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Use of crop rotation and irrigation methods helped Texicans maintain soil fertility and water supply.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Evaluate how environmental factors shaped Texican agricultural decisions.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming settlers used uniform farming methods without regard to local conditions.</p></div></div>",
