    "num": "11",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">11</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Map-Based Activity Prep</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing Texican Settlement Locations and Land Grants</h2><ul><li>Review maps showing Texican settlement clusters and land grant boundaries</li><li>Identify geographic features influencing settlement choices</li><li>Consider security and economic factors reflected in settlement patterns</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This activity prepares learners to analyze how geography, land grants, and frontier challenges shaped Texican settlements, setting the stage for group discussion. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Noting that many settlements are near rivers and mission sites on the map.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Mark on the map where you think settlements faced the greatest challenges and explain why.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Focusing only on political boundaries without considering physical geography or security.</p></div></div>",
