    "num": "12",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">12</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Discussion Prompt</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Frontier Challenges and Texican Responses</h2><ul><li>Discuss how Texicans balanced economic opportunity with security risks</li><li>Explore the role of cultural adaptation in managing frontier life</li><li>Consider how land grant policies shaped community resilience</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This discussion encourages learners to synthesize knowledge about Texican settlement patterns, lifestyle, and challenges, fostering deeper understanding through peer exchange. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A group might argue that cultural blending helped Texicans negotiate both Mexican law and frontier realities.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Share your analysis of how Texicans overcame frontier hardships and what lessons this offers for understanding early Texas history.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Treating economic, cultural, and security factors as isolated rather than interconnected.</p></div></div>",
