    "eyebrow": "Case Study Introduction",
    "num": "15",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">15</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Case Study Introduction</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Examining Texican Perspectives Through Primary Sources</h2><ul><li>Primary sources provide direct insight into Texican experiences</li><li>Government records and personal letters reveal political and cultural views</li><li>Analyzing language and context is key to understanding Texican perspectives</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">To grasp Texicans’ roles and identities, learners must engage with primary documents that capture their voices and viewpoints during the Texas Revolution (s2, s7). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter from a Texican soldier expressing conflicted feelings about independence illustrates personal perspectives.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Read a primary source excerpt and identify the author’s stance on Texas independence.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the historical context that shapes the tone and content of primary sources.</p></div></div>",
