    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">24</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Workshop Preview</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Document Analysis Workshop: What to Expect</h2><ul><li>Hands-on practice with Texican land grants, letters, and government records</li><li>Focus on identifying language, bias, and historical context</li><li>Collaborative discussion to deepen understanding</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This workshop will allow learners to apply critical analysis skills to authentic Texican primary sources, enhancing their grasp of early Texas history (s15, s17). <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s17\">[17]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Analyzing a land grant’s legal terms to understand Texican settlement rights.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Prepare questions or observations to share during the workshop.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Approaching documents without critical questions or context.</p></div></div>",
