    "eyebrow": "Role-Play Preparation",
    "num": "29",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">29</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Role-Play Preparation</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Simulating Texican-Native Negotiations</h2><ul><li>Learners will assume roles of Texican settlers and Native representatives</li><li>Objective: negotiate terms for land use, trade, or peace</li><li>Consider historical context, cultural priorities, and power dynamics</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Role-play helps learners embody perspectives and understand the complexity of frontier negotiations beyond abstract facts. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Texican negotiator might seek land access while a Comanche leader prioritizes protection of hunting grounds.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Prepare arguments and proposals reflecting your assigned group's interests and concerns.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring historical context or oversimplifying motivations can reduce role-play effectiveness.</p></div></div>",
