    "id": "slide42",
    "eyebrow": "Role-Play Execution",
    "num": "30",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">30</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Role-Play Execution</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Negotiation Simulation: Texicans and Native Tribes</h2><ul><li>Engage in dialogue representing your assigned group</li><li>Propose terms for land use, trade, or peace agreements</li><li>Respond to counteroffers and manage conflicts constructively</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This active exercise allows learners to practice negotiation skills and appreciate the complexity of frontier diplomacy. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican group offers livestock in exchange for safe passage through Comanche territory.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Negotiate terms that balance your group’s needs with those of the other party.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Dominating the conversation or refusing compromise can hinder realistic outcomes.</p></div></div>",
