    "id": "slide43",
    "eyebrow": "Post Role-Play Reflection",
    "num": "31",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">31</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Post Role-Play Reflection</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Analyzing Negotiation Outcomes and Perspectives</h2><ul><li>Discuss successes and challenges experienced during role-play</li><li>Identify how historical context influenced decisions</li><li>Reflect on Native and Texican perspectives and motivations</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Reflection solidifies learning by connecting role-play experiences to historical complexities and multiple viewpoints. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Learners note how mistrust limited agreement scope despite mutual benefits.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief summary comparing your role-play experience to historical accounts of Texican-Native relations.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Focusing only on winning the negotiation rather than understanding perspectives.</p></div></div>",
