    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">35</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Applying Frontier Interaction Concepts Today</h2><ul><li>Consider how historical Native-Texican relations inform modern cultural identities</li><li>Recognize ongoing impacts of displacement and cultural exchange</li><li>Reflect on the importance of multiple perspectives in history</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Understanding past interactions helps contextualize present-day cultural and social dynamics in Texas. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Modern Texan identity includes influences from Native heritage and settler history.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief reflection on how frontier history shapes contemporary Texas culture.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring historical continuity and present-day relevance.</p></div></div>",
