    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">36</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Transfer</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Extending Frontier Lessons to Other Contexts</h2><ul><li>Apply concepts of negotiation and cultural interaction to other historical frontiers</li><li>Analyze how power dynamics shape intercultural relations globally</li><li>Use critical source evaluation skills in diverse historical research</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texican-Native frontier experience provides a framework for understanding similar intercultural encounters worldwide. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Comparing Texican-Comanche relations with other settler-indigenous interactions in North America or beyond.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify a historical or contemporary example where negotiation and cultural exchange shaped outcomes.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Failing to recognize universal patterns or unique local factors.</p></div></div>",
